	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 3rd 5:49 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello friends.<br><br>Currently I have a level 13 Gnome Enchanter.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do have a main so this character has been twinked pretty well (194int, though charisma is suffering a little bit).  Well anyway, Im having trouble getting past level 13.  Im in Oasis of Marr right now..  I can't seem to get groups at Orc Highway, and when I try to solo things usually turn for the worse.  I've been trying to solo with charm, but I guess with 75 charisma I shouldn't expect much yet.  Normally I charm asps and let them fight caiman type monsters.  This all works but even with a high intelligence I run out of mana fast, after I charm a snake, and then cast Languid Pace, Ebbing Strength and Choke on what I attack.<br><br>So what Im asking here:<br> - Where is a good place to fight at in order to make level 16?<br> - Would you solo or group?<br> - If solo, what are the strategies I should be trying to execute?<br><br>And finally, a gear question.  I plan to buy the crude stein (25cha 10mana I think) once I no longer have a need for a weapon, which will bring my charisma up to 100.  Are there any good Int/Cha items out there, which are relatively cheap?  I always have the money to spend but am one who never likes to spend it :Þ  Or would I be better off just taking away and intelligence item and replacing it with a pure charisma item?  <br><br>Thanks ahead of time for any responses.<br><br>Keiten Shissar<br>13th Enchanter<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
