<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102764284781986></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102764284781986><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102764284781986>RE: Tash and Charm</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102764284781986#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 25th 8:33 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good question.&nbsp;&nbsp;Initially I would have just said that it helps only on the initial stick, BUT thinking about it more it seems like tash may actually help with the duration.<br><br>My understanding of how a charm spell works is like this.  First, to get the charm to stick, there are three factors: 1)your level vs. level of target, 2) MR of the target, and 3) target's save vs. your charisma.  So, obviously lowering the MR here helps you stick the charm, that I don't think anybody would disagree with.<br><br>Now, the target also gets a chance to break charm every tick, or every 6 seconds real-time.  I know that the monster rolls against your charisma.  Don't ask me about all the math and formulas, I just know that higher charisma helps your charm to not be broken.  But, my understanding is that the monster also gets to reroll for a resist based on his MR.  So, it would make sense that as long as tash stayed on it would make it harder for the target to break the charm.<br><br>This is a (somewhat) educated guess.  I know that most of what I have said is true but I'm not 100% on the ultimate question, whether tash helps charms last longer or not.  Anybody else feel free to comment or correct me if I'm wrong.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
