<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102764339382014></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102764339382014><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102764339382014>RE: Whirl till you Hurl</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102764339382014#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 25th 8:42 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I used to use it back in the day, but it didn't take long to realize it's limitations.&nbsp;&nbsp;A 12 second stun from a distance at level 12 seems too good to be true.  It pretty much is.  The main problem I had with it is that it NEVER lasted anywhere close to the 12 second max time.  The reason being is that, like root spells, the monster has a chance to break the spell every time he is hit.  Unlike root spells, melee damage is usually more than enough to break the spell.<br><br>So, in groups it is utterly useless since you'll likely have at least meleers slashing, crushing, piercing, kicking, bashing and whatever else.  Soloing it may last a little longer, but even our weak little pets can and will break the spell well-within 12 seconds.<br><br>I could feasably see it being useful in a short-duration crowd control situation where you might need to keep a MOB stunned, who is not being attacked by any players at the present time.  But, I think the point-blank color series is more practical for this situation and I'd be hard-pressed to see an enchanter make an open spell slot for this spell.<br><br>That's my take on the spell.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
