	   <tr><td colspan=2>Read this:<br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=13" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=13</a><br><br>The way I always did it was to start and be bound in or around Freeport.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'd make my way to Rivervale and get my honey jum first off.<br><br>Then I'd continue east to Surefall and visit the druid guy to get the nitrates for the regurgatonic quest.<br><br>I'd keep on east to Erudin and get Erud's tonic ... easy.<br><br>Then, I'd gate back to Freeport and boat over to Faydwer, stopping along the way to pick up the kiola nut on sisters island.<br><br>Once on Faydwer I'd go see the gnome about the regurgatonic and gate back to Freeport again.<br><br>Now another run to Western Karana where you feed the regurgatonic to the dog and you now have all four components.<br><br>Gate again to Freeport and take them to the bartender there.  He'll give you the book to give to Clurg.<br><br>Run down to Oggok and hand this to Clurg and you've got a stein.  It takes a while without a porter or by doing it 'old school' by not killing the fish, but it's an easy quest to do.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
