	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As an enchanter it is seldom that you get a chance to group with other enchanters or to ask them general questions.&nbsp;&nbsp;As I've been thinking about it, it's made me curious to know how others play the game compared to how I go about it.  So, I thought I'd take a little survey to see how different or similar all of our styles were.  Here we go.<br><br>1)What level are you? (I ask this because I've noticed strategies can change a lot over time.  What works at level 12 doesn't do so well at level 35 ...)<br><br>2)Do you mostly solo, partner, trio, or hunt in bigger groups?<br><br>3)If solo, do you charm, use a pet, root and nuke, or other?<br><br>4)If group, do you prefer single pulls or chaotic multiple aggro areas?<br><br>5)If group, do you prefer outdoor zones or dungeons?<br><br>6)Describe your typical spell lineup (i.e. what spells you keep memmed?).  If applicable, do the same thing for soloing, duoing, or grouping.<br><br>7)Is your enchanter your main character?<br><br>8)Lastly, write one sentence that describes why you like being an enchanter, or what appealed to you about the class and made you decide to play one.<br><br><br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
