<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102591476863635></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102591476863635><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102591476863635>RE: A little Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102591476863635#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 5th 8:30 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.44]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Quote:<br><br>more than 2 mobs (say 3 are pulled) if he were to cast fascination then mez two of the mobs after a few seconds would this cause too much aggro or would it be better then just mez'n from the start? <br><br>A few things.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm still shy of this level (46 right now) so I'm speaking based only on what I've learned from other sites and posts.  It is my understanding that Fascination won't stack with any of the single target mez spells.  Someone correct me if I'm wrong.  So, that wouldn't work.<br><br>As far as aggro, there's a couple points there.  Every mez spell actually has a small 'mem blur' component to it.  So that helps.  Also, as his tank, you are taunting every MOB before you break the mez, right?  This is invaluable.<br><br>He could still use a similar strategy though, if he wanted, wherein he reapplies Fascination as needed to the two 'resting' MOBs.  Of course, he'll probably want to tash and slow them while they are mezzed as well.<br><br>I think it all depends upon the situation and how the chanter wants to handle it.  Many prefer AoE mezzes, many despise them and would use single target mezzes.  As long as your chanter keeps your group alive and there aren't wild MOBs running about beating on the cleric, I say let him paint his own picture.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
