	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have never expressly charged for it, but if somebody wants to donate for Clarity I will accept the donation, as long as they look like they can afford it.<br><br>There are other ways to make better money in the game, especially as you get higher in level.<br><br>I think it's a karma thing in a way.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have way less respect for druids and wizzys who a)insist on a set price for ports and xlocs and especially for b)druids and wizzys who insist on pre-payment for ports.  I will purposely go out of my way to avoid being ported by these folks and try to find somebody else.  And when I do I will pay them fairly for their services.<br><br>I have a friend who plays a wizzy and makes it a rule to only 'port for donations'.  It seems like he runs into way more friendly folks who will voluntarily hand over much more than 10p for his services.  Of course he gets his share of people who give him nothing or 50 gold or something, but it all evens out in the end.<br><br>So, if you ask me, be nice about it.  Kindness often pays the best dividnends.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
