	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have noticed that problem in Umbral.<br><br>Mostly I rely on casting fetter before tash or slow.&nbsp;&nbsp;This lets me med and the mob won't run after me while its stuck.  Sitting sometimes agro's mobs so i try to get a feel for when it is safe to do so.  If i get summoned, i still have the option of backing out while its rooted and casting mem blur before sitting.<br><br>If the mob is resistant to root, then i wait for it to take about 10% damage before tashing and rooting.<br><br>If there's another chanter or shaman, I like to split up the tash and slow duties to lower try to lower the agro.<br><br>Best Regards,<br><br>Calanctus of Sol Ro<br>lvl 60 Phantasmist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>

